Crambus harrisi is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by Alexander Barrett Klots in 1967. It is found in North America, where it has been recorded from New Mexico and Texas.The length of the forewings is about 11.8 mm for males and 10.4 mm for females. The ground colour of the forewings is light brown. The hindwings are light brownish, slightly darker terminally and apically. Adults have been recorded on wing in August.